As shown in FT-IR spectra of Fig. 1b, in spite of the similarity with FPTA NPs, a new absorption peak at 1510 cm−1 originated from the N–O stretching vibration of –NO2 groups in FPTA NPs had generated [43,44]. Meanwhile, the UV–vis absorption spectrum of detection system of FPTA NPs plus NO2
                        − in an acidic environment exhibited a new absorption peak at 354 nm as well as the main peak centered at 265 nm (Fig. 6
                        ). The detection system accompanied by a visual color change from colorless to deep yellow (insert image in Fig. 6). This should be attributed to the formation of electron-withdrawing nitro, increasing the conjugation of nitroaromatic compounds.
